	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Slashdot Luclin Article</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=529449" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
<a href="http://www.slashdot.org" target="_blank">Slashdot</a> has posted <a href="http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=01/12/06/0255244&mode=nested" target="_blank">an article</a> regarding the Shadows of Luclin release. 
<blockquote>
<hr>
Ok, so what was the first day like? Well, the servers were down for most of the day, when they were supposed to just be down for a night. Then, when they came up, it seems that Sony did not provide enough network bandwidth for the patching storm that ensued, so no one could patch (and thus, no one could play) until a crittical mass of players gave up and went to bed. 
<P>
Worse, the patching program was intolerant of the network failures and would leave droppings that would prevent subsequent attempts to patch. I required 2 reboots, 5 file deletions and 2.5 hours to finally patch and run. 
<hr>
</blockquote>
<p>
Make sure you stop by there and give it a look-see.
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
