			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hey all, just thought I should follow up here, since next to Slashot, Everlore is one of my most frequently visited sites!<BR>
<BR>
Ignoring the &quot;this article sux!&quot; messages, I see a real theme here on Everlore. That is, &quot;hey, did you expect it to be perfect?&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Of course I didn't, and if you read my article clearly (and my followup postings to it) you will see that I'm quite happy with Everquest as a whole. I just think that Verant (and the rest of the gaming industry with them) has not figured out the mechanics of MMORPG software support and release engineering. This is a hard problem, and one that I expect the first dozen or so products to fail to pull off 100% correctly.<BR>
<BR>
Personally, I think there's going to be a legal challenge to this idea that you can sell someone a product and then up the system requirements mid-stream (this gets into lemon laws and arcane legal semantics I don't understand, so flame away if you like ;)<BR>
<BR>
I also think that within the month Verant will have 90% of the kinks worked out, and that's not bad for a major software release. Really, the only catch is that people who *did not upgrade* got whacked by the downtimes and many of the crash bugs (because in reality we all upgraded).<BR>
<BR>
I'm looking forward to the next generation of MMORPGs that solve these issues, but for now I'm quite happy to keep working on my HUM/WAR and IKS/NEC.<BR>
<BR>
Find my character on allakhazam and send a tell sometime!<BR>
<BR>
Thanks.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

