heres the real artical...<BR>
<BR>
Dateline San Deigo USA Dec 4th 2001.<BR>
<BR>
-&quot;EverQuest: Shadows of Lucin&quot; launched today marking the third expansion and first graphics upgrade to the vastly poplar on-line game. Although some growing pains occured, overall the upgrade was painless for the majority of prepared EQ gamers.<BR>
Those that did experience problems were not prepared due to the fact that those users are idiots and didn't match the new game specs to their existing computer. Instead they threatened law suits based on &quot;Customer Stupity&quot;. One begrudge EQ'er stated &quot;my 486 8meg ram with win95 can't play SoL. EQ sux, i'm going to play DAoC*, I can kill stuff there and get phat l3wt!&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
Overall this editor gives it 7 out of 10. once the minor fixes have been implemented look for that 7 to go up! Happy gaming!<BR>
<BR>
*Editors note: DAoC (Dark age of Camalot) is the game former EQ players go when they get pissy. They want someone to take notice of them and their stupidity so they leave acting like 6 year olds. Most EQ'er respond to this by saying &quot;thank gawd&quot; and wave at the departure of yet, another idiot.
