				All I hear is *****ing and moaning and all and all. If you expected to see everything go smooth on expansion day, your an idiot, pure and simple. And if you can't do a simple upgrade in ram or OS, well tough luck. I won't be penalized to get a better looking game because some are too lazy to do upgrades that don't cost that much.<BR>
<BR>
Most didn't even bother to go to EQ's official site and get the new patch client. The first thing I did when I saw errors on the one I had was to go to EQ to see whats up. Tells me to download this client instead. Two minutes later I was downloading files through the client and at 9:15pm I was online playing EQ.<BR>
<BR>
For your info. I'm playing with a P2 350 with 320MB of ram and a voodoo 3 card (i would of gotten a new card if I had problems) with 50% clipping plane on and half character models on and I have no problems playing.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
