				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				for all those souls who feel they can't afford to upgrade, check out www.pricewatch.com.  You can definitely get the system you specified for $600, less even.  You just need to know where to look.<BR>
<BR>
Regarding the future of everquest requiring a T1 line to your house... that would  rock.  Imagine what they could do with it!  And when a sizeable enough playerbase has that kind of setup to make it profitable, verant will make a BUSINESS decision on wether they will make that a requirement.  <BR>
<BR>
Verant is a company, they make these types of decisions for business reasons.  Everquest is not some charity or god given right.  Sure they may loose some customers due to this upgrade, but they are probably thinking more long term.  How to attract NEW customers.  How to retain the majority of their population in the long run.  If that means loosing the small segment of their player population that can not upgrade from windows 95, then I am certain those losses have been calculated intot he bigger equation.<BR>
<BR>
http://www.pricewatch.com<BR>
<BR>
check it out.  If you cant afford those prices, you should probably re-evaluate wether you can afford everquest at all.<BR>
